<br>
From what I hear, monks were the way they were pre-patch for at least 2 years or more, so it's no wonder many of the 2+ year old monks were very shocked and hurt by this, after becoming so accustomed to their class, and their role in game.<br>
<br>
So now what I ask, if they'll nerf monks like they have done, and do a straight nerf, not taking bits from here, and putting them somewhere else, just removing bits period....  Who's to say they won't do the same to another class?<br>
<br>
I'm an admitted alt-o-holic, I love trying all the different classes out, but where's my sense of assurance that I won't get attached to a class, just to be nerfed after putting months and months, literally weeks of played time into this class, setting myself up for another huge disappointment?<br>
<br>
What assurance do we have that, for the most part, the game is now &quot;balanced&quot; and another insanely controversial nerf for another class isn't in store in the future?<br>
<br>
This is just very unsettling to me, I just made a Beastlord, gonna try him out, where's my assurance I don't get to lvl 50 or something, and just start to really go full force to get to the ever glorious lvl 60 (soon to be 65 apparently) just for Verant to find they've made another blunder, and to nerf this character I've come to enjoy so much?<br>
<br>
I personally feel that as a paying customer, and with the time-sink involved with this game, we'd deserve some kind of &quot;future scope&quot; on what they have planned for other classes, hoping to avoid mistakenly getting attached to the &quot;doomed class&quot;.  I know I'm possibly over-dramaticizing these things, but EQ is so insanely addictive, it's hard not to get attached to a character you've made, and be proud of them, then when you get one of your nuts cut off, it's hard to say &quot;oh well, I won't miss it too much anyway&quot;. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskewert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skewert</A> at: 10/17/02 12:55:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unogem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nogem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/17/02 1:14:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=385.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feeling uneasy about starting any new chars now?</span><hr size=1> I'm only responding to the &quot;Who's to say they won't do the same to another class?&quot; thing as a rogue. My gear is 'ok' for my level. No where near end-game of course. With saying that maybe I havent seen all there is as far as my potential, but I've seen enough to make an few obsevations. <br>
<br>
In all honesty I dont see a nerf coming my way. Then again I suppose monks didnt see it coming either. As far as being a rogue...what could they really do to me? They cant change my defensive, my god. I'd be a damn int caster then. Doing something to my offense is working backwards(Wich I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> hope</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> they'd relize...hope.). There really is nothing else to me. Closest thing I've had to a nerf is the AC on luclin mobs. Who knows maybe down the line they'll shit thier pants over rogue evasion. Who's to say?<br>
<br>
I dont want to try and pretend to be a non-monk expert on monks, but just from friends in my guild and out of this change was simply wrong. After you've lived a life for so long to come and have a major part of it (exp game specificaly) is horrible. Coming from a class, who for the most part, is unable to solo past lvl 20...maybe it wont be so bad in the end. God forbid, you'll have to go lfg instead of going to FG and soloing. Welcome to my life.<br>
<br>
PS: Remmber any view on monks I've made is for the majority in reference to the exp/leveling side of the game. I may have commented on raid/pulling, but I would be lost on that subject.<br>
