<br>
this aside, yes you obviously arent a vet player, because monks have been slowly falling ever since kunark came out......right WHEN kunark came out a huge influx of ikky monks were made, obviously (fyi human > lizard ;) so they were nice enough to wait a few months after kunark to let the monks fall, using the iksar monk as a marketing ploy as they always do (look at beasties? what other class can level that fast? just wait, theyll get the shaft)<br>
<br>
the answer to your question is that no class is safe from being nerfed, because nerfing and changing around classes and altering the game is one way that verant keeps interest in it.......i mean look now, 10,000 warriors just got more interested in their class and rogues sure as hell are beaming with smiles, in fact they have been ever since late kunark/velious (just wait, theyll get the shaft, but they had a really hard shaft in the beginning, so VI needs to wait until everyones 'forgotten' that rogues did less dmg then warriors because backstab didnt even work)........<br>
<br>
the only way you can choose a class that you want to be able to solo with regardless of their nerfing (now i know im sticking my foot in my ass but oh well, its held true so far for the most part) is by picking a druid or a necro ;)<br>
<br>
in all honestly those are the only 2 classes that have always been able to solo regardless.......and no its not always been easy, but due to the nature of their class, they are able to 'bend' the way the game works and eventually they can kill things without too much risk and/or too much loss.........so progress for them, solo, has always been achievable......if this changes, their classes will be entirely broken, because the only reason they can solo is also the only reason they bring any benefit whatsoever (albeit, small) to a group......so choosing one of these 2 is a rather safe bet as far as choosing a class that will be solo capable........<br>
shaman is also a soloer now.......but wasnt exactly so forever<br>
<br>
if any of you say mage is a capable soloer or wizard, yer a noob, you havent been around long......but ill agree with you anyway because as the game is now, these 2 classes are also solo capable (but mage sucks pre-epic and pre-50......so i wouldnt bother really).........there was a point in time where melee's were solo capable.....and thats where monks shone, because back then, they still did enough damage to kill things faster then they could do enough serious damage back to the monk........and having a fungi or a regen along with mend to regain those (very limited amount of) HPs, made monk a solo practical class.......i believe VI didnt like that concept......they dont like when their players are happy, when they are able to solo if they cant find a group........VI just loves and rellishes in the amount of time ppl waste in 'getting exp groups' in order to get exp (hell it was impossible to get exp past 40 before kunark without a full group in guk or solb).......because they know that the time wasted to get the groups and get everything together and get situated far overweighs the amount of exp bonus gained in groups......and this all relates to more time wasted playing EQ which they think is the ultimate reason they retain their players........<br>
<br>
if any of you have played daoc or shadowbane beta, theres a really simple concept to those games that make them superior. (although i dont leave eq for daoc because SB is too close and i dont want to learn 2 new games in the span of half a year) that concept is that players will want to try out MANY of the different classes and play styles that they can imagine......that having more then 1 main would eventually be the wish of most players, if it was just possible......but in EQ its not.......<br>
99% of EQ players have tried more the 1 class, and have enjoyed more then 1 class equally, but have had to take 1 as their main......verant thinks that when this person is 'done' with their main.....having gotten all the loot, having gotten all the exp (funny how they added aa xp for yet another thing to 'achieve', and effectively level from 1 to 60 again), having done all the raids, verant thinks that these people will quit......fucking amazing that most of them stick behind and, despite the enourmous amount of work involved, most of them even start up a different class.......<br>
verant will never fucking get it will they.......<br>
and we'll all just keep paying......<br>
<br>
until shadowbane arrives anyway ;) <p><HR>
